			Session Pool Administration Sample

The "admin" application illustrates how to use the administrative API
to control the session pools and to retrieve the statistics through
PageCompiledServlet in Servlet Connectivity for Tuxedo.

REQUIREMENT
===========
Any Web Application Server with Servlet JSDK 1.1 or above
Jolt 1.2

INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
=========================

1. Install the Jolt class library and Servlet Connectivity for Tuxedo class
   library to the web application server.

2. Copy all JHTML files to the public HTML directory (e.g.
   $WEBLOGIC/myserver/public_html for WebLogic):

	PoolList.jhtml
	PoolAdmin.jhtml

3. To get a list of session pools, use the following URL in your
   favorite browser:

	http://mywebserver:8080/PoolList.jhtml

REFERENCES
==========
1. Java Servlets
	http://jserv.java.sun.com/products/java-server/documentation/
		webserver1.1/index_developer.html

2. Servlet Interest Group:
	servlet-interest@java.sun.com
